5 F. Parcel fee. The governing authority of East Baton Rouge Parish district
6 may impose and collect a parcel fee within the district subject to and in accordance
7 with the provisions of this Subsection:.
8 (1) The amount of the fee shall be as requested by duly adopted resolution
9 of the board. The fee, however, shall not be less than one hundred dollars per parcel
10 per year and not more than one hundred fifty dollars per parcel per year for lots
11 zoned for residential use.
12 * * *
13 (3)(a) The fee shall be imposed only after the question of its imposition has
14 been approved by a majority of the registered voters of the district voting at an
15 election held for that purpose in accordance with the Louisiana Election Code. At
16 least thirty days prior to any election held to approve imposition of a parcel fee, the
17 board shall mail notification of the upcoming election to each registered voter of the
18 district and to the owner of each parcel if the owner is not a registered voter of the
19 district. During the term of the fee, the board may increase the fee one time during
20 each subsequent calendar year, without election, not to exceed ten percent of the
21 amount imposed during the previous calendar year; however, the amount of the fee
22 shall not exceed the maximum amount authorized in this Subsection. No other
23 election shall be required except as provided by this Paragraph.
24 (b) The initial election on the question of the imposition of the fee shall be
25 held at the same time as a regularly scheduled election in the parish of East Baton
26 Rouge.
27 (c) The fee shall expire ten years from its initial levy at the time provided in
28 the proposition authorizing the fee, not to exceed ten years, but may be renewed as
29 provided in Subparagraph (a) of this Paragraph. If the fee is renewed, the term of the
