12 Section that the additional law enforcement personnel and services provided by the
13 district shall be supplemental to and not in lieu of personnel and services provided
14 in the district by the city of Baker and the city of Baton Rouge and parish of East
15 Baton Rouge.
16 (2) If the district ceases to exist, any funds of the district shall be transmitted
17 to the governing authority of the city of Baton Rouge and parish of East Baton
18 Rouge Baker and shall be used for law enforcement purposes in the area included
19 within the district.
20 J. Indemnification and exculpation. (1) The district shall indemnify its
21 officers and board members to the fullest extent permitted by R.S. 12:227, as fully
22 as if the district were a nonprofit corporation governed thereby and as may be
23 provided in the district's bylaws.
24 (2) No board member or officer shall be liable to the district or to any
25 individual who resides, owns property, visits, or otherwise conducts business in the
26 district for monetary damages for breach of his duties as a board member or officer,
27 provided that this provision shall not eliminate or limit the liability of a board
28 member or officer for any of the following:
29 (a) Acts or omissions not in good faith or which involve intentional
30 misconduct or a knowing violation of law.
